{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Sponge","content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Grease and line base of a round cake tin (Ø 20 cm).","Place pistachios in mixing bowl then roughly chop <b>2 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer to a bowl, remove 2 Tbsp of larger chunks to a smaller bowl then set both aside.","Place cardamom and almonds in mixing bowl then grind <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place lemon peel and 30 g sugar in mixing bowl then grind <b>15 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add remaining 120 g sugar and butter then cream <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add eggs and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add flour, reserved almond mixture, baking powder, rose water and salt then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add large bowl of reserved chopped pistachios and mix <b>20 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to prepared tin then bake for 40-50 minutes (170°C) until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl.","Leave cake to stand for 5 minutes in tin. Meanwhile, make syrup"]},{"title":"Syrup","content":["Place lemon juice and sugar in mixing bowl then heat <b>2 min\/90°C\/speed 1.5<b>. Meanwhile, poke holes in the cake surface using a cocktail stick. Drizzle syrup over cake, allowing it to seep into the holes then leave to cool. Clean mixing bowl.","Once cool, remove from tin and transfer to a serving plate or cake stand."]},{"title":"Icing and Decoration","content":["Place mascarpone, icing sugar and rose water in mixing bowl then mix <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong> then, without setting a time, and without measuring cup, whip <strong>speed 3<\/strong> until softly whipped, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping. Spoon over cake surface.","Garnish with a sprinkling of reserved chopped pistachios and edible rose petals (if using) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Sponge","content":["60 g pistachio nuts, unsalted, shelled","½ tsp ground cardamom","250 g blanched almonds","1 lemon, thin peelings of skin","150 g light brown sugar","200 g unsalted butter, soft, plus extra for greasing","4 medium eggs","100 g plain flour","1 tsp baking powder","2 tsp rose water","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Syrup","content":["40 g lemon juice","30 g light brown sugar"]},{"title":"Icing and Decoration","content":["200 g mascarpone","40 g icing sugar","½ tsp rose water","edible rose petals              (optional)"]}],"id":"r340865","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-XkdBSAZlcxk\/XZWpzPCPqNI\/AAAAAAAAfPM\/kZRCyr91aos73efSzGBnQPJVo4TV0vm_gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6hSazvqws0rGsKBC.png","title":"Persian Love Cake","publishedAt":"2018-06-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10.2 g","fat":"36.9 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"27.1 g","calories":"2027 kJ \/ 488 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cake tin (Ø 20 cm), baking paper, skewer, serving plate, cocktail stick, oven","hintsAndTricks":["A version of this floral scented cake was originally made by a Persian woman in the hope that the Prince would fall in love with her. With beautiful colours and rich flavours, its hard not to love!","For an even more intense flavour, make your own ground cardamon by freshly grinding cardamom pods."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 15m","12 slices"]}